
# Web Attack Investigation Report 🔐

**Platform:** LetsDefend  
**Date:** May 2026  
**Investigations:** Open Redirection | Brute Force Attack

---

## Introduction

This report documents two hands-on web attack investigations completed in the LetsDefend SOC Analyst lab. Each investigation involved analysing real Apache access logs, identifying attacker behaviour phase by phase, and extracting key Indicators of Compromise (IOCs) using Linux command-line tools and regex pattern matching.

---

## Investigation 1 — Open Redirection 🔴

### What is Open Redirection?

An Open Redirect vulnerability occurs when a web application uses unvalidated user input to redirect users to external URLs. Attackers exploit this to send victims from a trusted domain to a malicious site — commonly used in phishing campaigns.

**Log File:**
```
/root/Desktop/QuestionFiles/Open-Redirection/access.log
```

---

### Phase 1 — Reconnaissance

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Attacker IP | `254.198.150.19` |
| Date | 26/Apr/2023 |
| Time Range | 03:44:47 — 19:45:14 |

The attacker browsed the application normally, testing different `postId` values to map out which pages existed and how the server responded.

**Evidence from log:**
```
254.198.150.19 [26/Apr/2023:19:44:47] GET /post?postId=9  → 200 OK
254.198.150.19 [26/Apr/2023:19:44:47] GET /post?postId=0  → 404 Not Found
254.198.150.19 [26/Apr/2023:19:44:47] GET /post?postId=   → 400 Bad Request
254.198.150.19 [26/Apr/2023:19:45:12] GET /post?postId=16 → 404 Not Found
254.198.150.19 [26/Apr/2023:19:45:12] GET /post?postId=10 → 200 OK
```

**Command used:**
```bash
cat /root/Desktop/QuestionFiles/Open-Redirection/access.log
```

---

### Phase 2 — Exploitation

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Attacker IP | `86.236.188.85` |
| Exploitation Start | 27/Apr/2023 15:45:22 |
| Parameter Attacked | `postId` |

A new IP appeared and began injecting URL-encoded external domains into the `postId` parameter using multiple filter bypass techniques.

**Evidence from log:**
```
86.236.188.85 [27/Apr/2023:15:45:22] GET /post?postId=%2f%09%2fexample%2ecom       → 400
86.236.188.85 [27/Apr/2023:15:45:22] GET /post?postId=%2f%2f%5cexample%2ecom       → 400
86.236.188.85 [27/Apr/2023:15:45:23] GET /post?postId=https%3a%2f%2fgoogle%2ecom   → 400
86.236.188.85 [27/Apr/2023:15:45:24] GET /post?postId=%2f%2fwhitelist%40google%2ecom → 400
```

**Bypass techniques used:**

| Encoded | Decoded | Technique |
|---------|---------|-----------|
| `%2f%2f` | `//` | Double slash redirect |
| `%5c` | `\` | Backslash bypass |
| `%09` | TAB | Tab character bypass |
| `%2e%2e` | `..` | Path traversal |
| `@` trick | `whitelist@google.com` | Domain bypass |
| `https%3a%2f%2f` | `https://` | Protocol confusion |

**Detection command:**
```bash
grep -E "postId=.*(https?|%2f%2f|%5c|%2e%2e|%09)" \
  /root/Desktop/QuestionFiles/Open-Redirection/access.log
```

---

### Summary — Open Redirection

| Finding | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Recon IP | `254.198.150.19` |
| Attacker IP | `86.236.188.85` |
| Parameter Attacked | `postId` |
| Exploitation Start | `27/Apr/2023 15:45:22` |
| Targets | `google.com`, `example.com`, `localdomain.pw` |
| Server Response | 400 Bad Request — all blocked |
| Outcome | ❌ Attack unsuccessful |

